## Two's Complement (8-bit)

### Signed → Binary

```python
format((-74) & 0xff, '08b')
# 10110110
```

### Binary → Signed

```python
x = int("10110110", 2)
x - 256 if x & 0x80 else x
# -74
```

---

## Two's Complement (General)

### Signed Integer → N-bit Binary

```python
n = -10
bits = 8

format(n & ((1 << bits) - 1), f'0{bits}b')
```

### Binary → Signed Integer

```python
bits = 8
x = int("11110110", 2)

if x & (1 << (bits - 1)):
    x -= (1 << bits)

print(x)
# -10
```

