## Useful Reverse Engineering One-Liners

### Hex Dump

```python
data.hex()
```

### Printable Strings

```python
''.join(chr(c) for c in data if 32 <= c <= 126)
```

### Byte Frequency

```python
from collections import Counter

Counter(data)
```

### Reverse Bytes

```python
data[::-1]
```

### MD5

```python
import hashlib

hashlib.md5(data).hexdigest()
```

### SHA256

```python
hashlib.sha256(data).hexdigest()
```

